This recipe is so basic, but the star of this dish is the sausage which comes out incredibly tender when done. I used hot Italian sausage and omitted the crushed red pepper flakes, and used one red and one yellow pepper instead of the green. Made terrific Italian sausage sandwiches!

Rating: 4
This recipe turned out wonderfully. It is definitely going to be added as one of our favorites! However, I made a few changes to make it my own!: Instead of 2 green peppers, I substituted one poblano pepper and 2 yellow peppers. I realized too late that I ran out of oregeno, so I used 2 teaspoons of Emeril's Chicken rub (it had oregeno in it!) I also did 1 lb mild sausage and 1 lb hot italian sausage. I mildly browned the onions in a pan before adding it to the mixture. I increased the olive oil to 6 tablespoons. The juices at the bottom of the dish was my favorite part! I served it with large, doughy white rolls to absorb all the juices. I also turned up the temp to 375F and it was perfectly cooked after 45 minutes.Enjoy!!!!!

