Rating: 0
SAUSAGE AND PEPPER BAKE It was my lucky day. My small, owner-owned meat market had made hot Italian sausage. Peppers, onions, olive oil, sausage....perfect. The plump, succulent sausage cooked perfectly in a little over 45 minutes. What is a host to do while waiting for the peppers and onions to cook? Watch the first two-hour episode of Ken Burns The War ON PBS is an option. Watching your guests getting drunk and calling a taxi for them is less appealing. Onions and peppers give off water when they cook, and cook and cook and cook and cook, and cook and oven roasted never, ever get the well done, slightly charred goodness of sauté...at least not according to this recipe. Was anyone in the test kitchen? Apparently not. Don't try this disaster. If you have to go to the trouble of browning the sausages just add some peppers and onions and spices and have a great dinner. DON'T TRY THIS AT HOME.

