Rating: 1
I was disappointed with this recipe. Liked the time-saver of not having to saute the peppers and onions, but by baking instead of sauteing you lose out on the ever-so-important caramelization process. Also, the vegetables release quite a bit of water which sit at the bottom of the baking dish. Yuck. Had the vegetables been sauted, much of the water would evaporate and the peppers and onions would take on more desirable color and flavor. I'll stick with the traditional saute method next time.

